  "text": "MDA assay. The level of MDA was measured as described previously [CITATION_1] . MDA in the plasma was measured using HPLC (Gilson) equipped with a Spherisorb ODS 5 μm column (Waters Corporation, USA). Fifty μl of the plasma were mixed with 50 μl of 0.05% butylated hydroxytoluen, 400 μl of 0.44 mol/l phosphoric acid solution, and 100 μl of thiobarbituric acid (TBA) solution. The samples were then incubated in 100°C water bath for 1 hr. After incubation, the TBA-MDA precipitate was extracted with n-butanol. Aliquots of 100 μl were then removed from the n-butanol layer and injected into the HPLC system. Standards and quality control samples were prepared using 97% 1,1,3,3-tetraethoxypropane (0, 0.125, 0.5, 1.0, and 2.0 μmol/l).",
